race.comment: SUJEED (1) settled well back and was beaten 3.5 lengths over 1200m on the turf here two weeks ago. Found more like his best and is yet to miss the placings from four starts at this track. Has a wide gate but is suitably placed back in grade with the 3kg claim. ARIYAH (6) led and won her Maiden here and then wasn't too far away 7 days ago in a 58 on the turf. She will skip across and ride the speed and has plenty of scope for improvement. STARSARISE (3) brings good form over shorter sprints on the turf. She just missed in a CL1 at Eagle Farm three back and has trialled well here since last seen. Has some gear changes and has won on the all-weather. Has claims. GREY IMPACT (4) has trialled three times in town for her return to the racetrack. Gets in well with the 3kg claim and is proven fresh. Keep safe.
